description:
I've got a dataset including a xsd:boolean datatype. When I query Virtuoso via Sparql, sometimes I get my data as booleans and sometimes as integers, depending on the query. Details are as below.
Virtuoso version:
OpenLink Virtuoso Universal Server
Version 07.20.3214-pthreads for Linux as of Oct  1 2015

Given the dataset as below:
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix mp: <http://localhost/my/prefix#> .

<abb8616d-502d-4f69-9c90-b0c4d0574343>
    mp:mystring "stringvalue"^^xsd:string ;
    mp:myboolean "false"^^xsd:boolean .

when I execute the following Query:
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX mp: <http://localhost/my/prefix#>

SELECT ?id ?mystring ?myboolean WHERE {
    ?id mp:mystring ?mystring .
    ?id mp:myboolean ?myboolean .
    FILTER (?mystring = "stringvalue"^^xsd:string)
}

I get the myboolean as xsd:boolean:
{
    'id': {
        'type': 'uri',
        'value': 'abb8616d-502d-4f69-9c90-b0c4d0574343'
    },
    'myboolean': {
        'datatype': 'http: //www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean',
        'type': 'typed-literal',
        'value': '0'
    },
    'mystring': {
        'datatype': 'http: //www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string',
        'type': 'typed-literal',
        'value': 'stringvalue'
    }
}

But with the following query:
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX mp: <http://localhost/my/prefix#>

SELECT ?id ?mystring ?myboolean WHERE {
    ?id mp:mystring ?mystring .
    ?id mp:myboolean ?myboolean .
    FILTER (?myboolean = "false"^^xsd:boolean)
}

it is returned as xsd:integer:
{
    'mystring': {
        'value': 'stringvalue',
        'datatype': 'http: //www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string',
        'type': 'typed-literal'
    },
    'myboolean': {
        'value': '0',
        'datatype': 'http: //www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer',
        'type': 'typed-literal'
    },
    'id': {
        'value': 'abb8616d-502d-4f69-9c90-b0c4d0574343',
        'type': 'uri'
    }
}

I've checked that against the source release 7.2.1 and also against code from develop/7 branch and the behavior is the same.
